          <w:szCs w:val="22"/>
        </w:rPr>
        <w:t xml:space="preserve">A single HTML file that runs in any browser — no install, no login, no internet needed. Open it and it works: project it in a lecture, embed it in your VLE, or email it to students. It turns the core models of intermediate macro into something students manipulate directly rather than read about.</w:t>
